{
  "text": "Furthermore, we also have identified some peaks common to the midpiece and the tail (~1033,~1171 and 1232 cm −1 ). Thẽ 1033 cm −1 peak has not yet been described in sperm cells but was found in other cells mainly assigned to proteins [CITATION_1] . The other two peaks have been previously assigned to DNA bases, proteins and lipids [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The clear discrimination of the regions in the PCA analysis, have confirmed our observations in the mean spectra and might not only reflect the variance between different patterns in the spectra, but also may be supported by the presence or absence of characteristic peaks in some regions, ultimately reflecting a specific fingerprint for each region.",
  "correct_citation": {
